# Job Tracker — project context

Local-first Flask + SQLite job-application tracker (`jobtracker/` package).
Owner: Rami (GitHub `ramizil`), an automation/performance test specialist using
this to manage his job search. UI language is English with bilingual (EN+HE)
AI output.

## Architecture conventions

- **Config**: all settings live in the project-root `.env`, loaded by
  `jobtracker/config.py`. To add a setting: add it to `EDITABLE_KEYS`, the
  module globals, `reload()`, and `current_settings()` — the Settings UI and
  its POST handler pick it up automatically. The running server caches config;
  it reloads on Settings save (`update_env_file()`), not on manual `.env` edits.
- **DB migrations**: add new columns to `EXTRA_COLUMNS` in `jobtracker/db.py`
  (auto `ALTER TABLE` on `init_db()`). Never edit the base schema for additions.
- **AI providers**: `jobtracker/ai.py` dispatches via `_generate()` to
  gemini | openai | anthropic | groq | cursor. With `AI_FALLBACK=1`, a failed
  provider transparently falls back to the other configured ones
  (`_FALLBACK_ORDER`). Cursor has no native chat API — it goes
  through a local OpenAI-compatible proxy (`cursor-agent-api`, port 8080,
  model `auto`); `start.command` auto-starts it when `AI_PROVIDER=cursor`.
  Groq uses the OpenAI SDK against `https://api.groq.com/openai/v1`.
  Web-search grounding and voice transcription are **Gemini-only**; other
  providers must degrade gracefully (ungrounded fallback, readable `AIError`).
- **Bilingual AI output**: never ask a model for mixed "English — עברית"
  strings (RTL/LTR interleaving breaks rendering). Return **separate fields**
  (`verdict`/`verdict_he`, `{en, he}` objects, `company_brief.en`/`he`) and
  render with the `.bi` two-column grid (EN left/LTR, HE right/RTL) in templates.
- **Backward compatibility**: analysis/artefact JSON is persisted in SQLite.
  Templates must handle both old and new stored shapes (feature-detect fields,
  e.g. `{% if q.requirement_he %}`).
- **Error handling**: AI features raise `AIError` with a user-readable message
  that the UI flashes; features never hard-crash the page.

## Testing changes

- Use the project venv: `./.venv/bin/python -c "..."` smoke tests.
- For template changes, render real pages via
  `jobtracker.web.create_app().test_client()` and assert on the HTML.
- Restore any DB rows a test mutates (the DB holds real application data).
